  "text": "Image: Black Wings Game Studio/Sega via PolygonJazz Stewart is a Gaming Journalist and multimedia creator passionate about storytelling and game design. When he isn’t writing, he’s gaming; when he’s not gaming, he wishes he were.Working at the flower shop in Persona 5: The Phantom X is a part-time job that will sometimes require you to answer questions to do the job “correctly.”This mechanic is similar to the classroom questions and answers that have been prevalent in the Persona franchise since Persona 3. However, the mechanics are a bit different in this take on the Persona formula, as you have an infinite number of tries to get the correct answer.Persona 5: The Phantom X flower shop questions and answersImage: Black Wings Game Studio/Sega via PolygonPersona 5: The Phantom X’s randomness can be brutal, and you can go through multiple days of action points only to never even get the indicator that you can work at the flower shop. When you can work at the flower shop, you might not even have to answer a question.Here’s a list of questions we were asked while working at the Flower Shop, along with their correct answers. We will update this list as we continue to enjoy the game:QuestionAnswerThey want something modest to convey their love. Which flower would you suggest?White Lily of the ValleyThe request is for pink flowers to honor an occasion.Pink CarnationsThe next request wants large flowers with a mild scent.Golden GerberaPersona 5: The Phantom X flower shop question rewardsCompleting a shift at the flower shop increases Wonder’s Kindness stat. Choosing the correct answer doesn’t provide any bonus rewards, as you still get the same amount of kindness points, money, and Meta Jewels.Suppose you’re trying to get the most out of your time with Persona 5: The Phantom X. In that case, our guides can thoroughly explain the game’s iteration of Confidants, also known as Synergy Bonds, let you know the best gifts to give your potential romance candidates, and even answer some of the simpler questions, like about the protagonist’s canon name and daily reset time.",
