e were.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eWorking at the \u003cstrong\u003eflower shop\u003c/strong\u003e in \u003cem\u003ePersona 5: The Phantom X\u003c/em\u003e is a part-time job that will sometimes require you to answer questions to do the job “correctly.”\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThis mechanic is similar to the \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/guides/609183/persona-5-phantom-x-p5x-classroom-answers-questions\"\u003eclassroom questions and answers\u003c/a\u003e that have been prevalent in the \u003cem\u003ePersona\u003c/em\u003e franchise since \u003cem\u003ePersona 3\u003c/em\u003e. However, the mechanics are a bit different in this take on the \u003cem\u003ePersona\u003c/em\u003e formula, as you have an \u003cstrong\u003einfinite number of tries to get the correct answer\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp id=\"persona-5-the-phantom-x-flower-shop-questions-and-answers\"\u003e\u003ch2\u003ePersona 5: The Phantom X flower shop questions and answers\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/p5x2.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0,0,100,100\" data-pswp-height=\"1440\" data-pswp-width=\"2560\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Wonder being asked a question in the Flower Shop in Persona 5 The Phantom X\" data-chromatic=\"ignore\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(max-width: 639px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 50vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/p5x2.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=256 256w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/p5x2.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=376 376w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/p5x2.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=384 384w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/p5x2.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=415 415w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/p5x2.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=480 480w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/p5x2.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=540 540w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/p5x2.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=640 640w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/p5x2.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=750 750w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/p5x2.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=828 828w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/p5x2.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1080 1080w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/p5x2.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1200 1200w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/p5x2.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1440 1440w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/p5x2.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1920 1920w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/p5x2.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2048 2048w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/p5x2.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400 2400w\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/p5x2.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ccite\u003eImage: Black Wings Game Studio/Sega via Polygon\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003ePersona 5: The Phantom X\u003c/em\u003e’s randomness can be brutal, and you can go through multiple days of action points only to never even get the indicator that you can work at the flower shop. When you can work at the flower shop, you might not even have to answer a question.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eHere’s a list of questions we were asked while working at the Flower Shop, along with their correct answers. We will update this list as we continue to enjoy the game:\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ctable\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003cth\u003e\u003ch3\u003eQuestion\u003c/h3\u003e\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth\u003e\u003ch3\u003eAnswer\u003c/h3\u003e\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003eThey want something modest to convey their love. Which flower would you suggest?\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003eWhite Lily of the Valley\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003eThe request is for pink flowers to honor an occasion.\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003ePink Carnations\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003eThe next request wants large flowers with a mild scent.\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003eGolden Gerbera\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp id=\"persona-5-the-phantom-x-flower-shop-question-rewards\"\u003e\u003ch2\u003ePersona 5: The Phantom X flower shop question rewards\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eCompleting a shift at the flower shop increases Wonder’s Kindness stat. \u003cstrong\u003eChoosing the correct answer doesn’t provide any bonus rewards\u003c/strong\u003e, as you still get the same amount of kindness points, money, and Meta Jewels.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eSuppose you’re trying to get the most out of your time with \u003cem\u003ePersona 5: The Phantom X. \u003c/em\u003eIn that case, our guides can thoroughly explain the game’s iteration of Confidants, also known as \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/persona-5-phantom-x-guides/610797/p5x-romance-synergy-bonds-social-links-confidants\"\u003eSynergy Bonds\u003c/a\u003e, let you know the \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/persona-5-phantom-x-guides/610722/best-preferred-gifts-give-p5x-synergy\"\u003ebest gifts to give\u003c/a\u003e your potential romance candidates, and even answer some of the simpler questions, like about the \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/guides/609030/persona-5-phantom-x-p5x-canon-protagonist-name-change-how-to\"\u003eprotagonist’s canon name\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/guides/609513/persona-5-phantom-x-p5x-reset-daily-weekly-times\"\u003edaily reset time\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
